        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 7 at 2:47PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 246 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles south of Florence, or 26 miles west of Pueblo, moving southeast
at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Beulah, Wetmore, and Oak Ridge Burn Scar.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
